{"nodes":[{"content":"Windows App Certification Kit tests","pos":[3,38]},{"content":"\\[ Updated for UWP apps on Windows 10.","pos":[40,78]},{"content":"For Windows 8.x articles, see the <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>archive<ept id=\"p1\">](http://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/p/?linkid=619132)</ept> \\]","pos":[79,174],"source":" For Windows 8.x articles, see the [archive](http://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/p/?linkid=619132) \\]"},{"content":"The Windows App Certification Kit contains a number of tests that can help ensure that your app is ready to be published on the Windows Store.","pos":[176,318]},{"content":"Deployment and launch tests","pos":[323,350]},{"content":"Monitors the app during certification testing to record when it crashes or hangs.","pos":[352,433]},{"content":"Background","pos":[439,449]},{"content":"Apps that stop responding or crash can cause the user to lose data and have a poor experience.","pos":[451,545]},{"content":"We expect apps to be fully functional without the use of Windows compatibility modes, AppHelp messages, or compatibility fixes.","pos":[547,674]},{"content":"Apps must not list DLLs to load in the HKEY\\-LOCAL\\-MACHINE\\\\Software\\\\Microsoft\\\\Windows NT\\\\CurrentVersion\\\\Windows\\\\AppInit\\-DLLs registry key.","pos":[676,822]},{"content":"Test details","pos":[828,840]},{"content":"We test the app resilience and stability throughout the certification testing.","pos":[842,920]},{"content":"The Windows App Certification Kit calls <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt><bpt id=\"p2\">**</bpt>IApplicationActivationManager::ActivateApplication<ept id=\"p2\">**</ept><ept id=\"p1\">](https://msdn.microsoft.com/library/windows/desktop/Hh706903)</ept> to launch apps.","pos":[922,1095],"source":"The Windows App Certification Kit calls [**IApplicationActivationManager::ActivateApplication**](https://msdn.microsoft.com/library/windows/desktop/Hh706903) to launch apps."},{"content":"For <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>ActivateApplication<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> to launch an app, User Account Control (UAC) must be enabled and the screen resolution must be at least 1024 x 768 or 768 x 1024.","pos":[1096,1253],"source":" For **ActivateApplication** to launch an app, User Account Control (UAC) must be enabled and the screen resolution must be at least 1024 x 768 or 768 x 1024."},{"content":"If either condition is not met, your app will fail this test.","pos":[1254,1315]},{"content":"Corrective actions","pos":[1321,1339]},{"content":"Make sure UAC is enabled on the test computer.","pos":[1341,1387]},{"content":"Make sure you are running the test on a computer with large enough screen.","pos":[1389,1463]},{"content":"If your app fails to launch and your test platform satisfies the prerequisites of <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt><bpt id=\"p2\">**</bpt>ActivateApplication<ept id=\"p2\">**</ept><ept id=\"p1\">](https://msdn.microsoft.com/library/windows/desktop/Hh706903)</ept>, you can troubleshoot the problem by reviewing the activation event log.","pos":[1465,1706],"source":"If your app fails to launch and your test platform satisfies the prerequisites of [**ActivateApplication**](https://msdn.microsoft.com/library/windows/desktop/Hh706903), you can troubleshoot the problem by reviewing the activation event log."},{"content":"To find these entries in the event log:","pos":[1707,1746]},{"content":"Open eventvwr.exe and navigate to the Application and Services Log\\\\Microsoft\\\\Windows\\\\Immersive-Shell folder.","pos":[1752,1863]},{"content":"Filter the view to show Event Ids: 5900-6000.","pos":[1868,1913]},{"content":"Review the log entries for info that might explain why the app didn't launch.","pos":[1918,1995]},{"content":"Troubleshoot the file with the problem, identify and fix the problem.","pos":[1997,2066]},{"content":"Rebuild and re-test the app.","pos":[2067,2095]},{"content":"You can also check if a dump file was generated in the Windows App Certification Kit log folder that can be used to debug your app.","pos":[2096,2227]},{"content":"Platform Version Launch test","pos":[2232,2260]},{"content":"Checks that the Windows app can run on a future version of the OS.","pos":[2262,2328]},{"content":"This test has historically been only applied to the Desktop app workflow, but this is now enabled for the Store and Universal Windows Platform (UWP) workflows.","pos":[2329,2488]},{"content":"Background","pos":[2494,2504]},{"content":"Operating system version info has restricted usage for the Windows Store.","pos":[2506,2579]},{"content":"This has often been incorrectly used by apps to check OS version so that the app can provide users with functionality that is specific to an OS version.","pos":[2580,2732]},{"content":"Test details","pos":[2738,2750]},{"content":"The Windows App Certification Kit uses the HighVersionLie to detect how the app checks the OS version.","pos":[2752,2854]},{"content":"If the app crashes, it will fail this test.","pos":[2855,2898]},{"content":"Corrective action","pos":[2904,2921]},{"content":"Apps should use Version API helper functions to check this.","pos":[2923,2982]},{"content":"See <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Operating System Version<ept id=\"p1\">](https://msdn.microsoft.com/library/windows/desktop/ms724832)</ept> for more information.","pos":[2983,3096],"source":" See [Operating System Version](https://msdn.microsoft.com/library/windows/desktop/ms724832) for more information."},{"content":"Background tasks cancellation handler validation","pos":[3101,3149]},{"content":"This verifies that the app has a cancellation handler for declared background tasks.","pos":[3151,3235]},{"content":"There needs to be a dedicated function that will be called when the task is cancelled.","pos":[3236,3322]},{"content":"This test is applied only for deployed apps.","pos":[3323,3367]},{"content":"Background","pos":[3373,3383]},{"content":"Store apps can register a process that runs in the background.","pos":[3385,3447]},{"content":"For example, an email app may ping a server from time to time.","pos":[3448,3510]},{"content":"However, if the OS needs these resources, it will cancel the background task, and apps should gracefully handle this cancellation.","pos":[3511,3641]},{"content":"Apps that don't have a cancellation handler may crash or not close when the user tries to close the app.","pos":[3642,3746]},{"content":"Test details","pos":[3752,3764]},{"content":"The app is launched, suspended and the non-background portion of the app is terminated.","pos":[3766,3853]},{"content":"Then the background tasks associated with this app are cancelled.","pos":[3854,3919]},{"content":"The state of the app is checked, and if the app is still running then it will fail this test.","pos":[3920,4013]},{"content":"Corrective action","pos":[4019,4036]},{"content":"Add the cancellation handler to your app.","pos":[4038,4079]},{"content":"For more information see <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Support your app with background tasks<ept id=\"p1\">](https://msdn.microsoft.com/library/windows/apps/Mt299103)</ept>.","pos":[4080,4204],"source":" For more information see [Support your app with background tasks](https://msdn.microsoft.com/library/windows/apps/Mt299103)."},{"content":"App count","pos":[4209,4218]},{"content":"This verifies that an app package (APPX, app bundle) contains one application.","pos":[4220,4298]},{"content":"This was changed in the kit to be a standalone test.","pos":[4299,4351]},{"content":"Background","pos":[4357,4367]},{"content":"This test was implemented as per Store policy.","pos":[4369,4415]},{"content":"Test details","pos":[4421,4433]},{"content":"For Windows Phone 8.1 apps the test verifies the total number of appx packages in the bundle is <ph id=\"ph1\">&amp;lt;</ph> 512, there is only one main package in the bundle, and that the architecture of the main package in the bundle is marked as ARM or neutral.","pos":[4435,4675],"source":"For Windows Phone 8.1 apps the test verifies the total number of appx packages in the bundle is &lt; 512, there is only one main package in the bundle, and that the architecture of the main package in the bundle is marked as ARM or neutral."},{"content":"For Windows 10 apps the test verifies that the revision number in the version of the bundle is set to 0.","pos":[4677,4781]},{"content":"Corrective action","pos":[4787,4804]},{"content":"Ensure the app package and bundle meet requirements above in Test details.","pos":[4806,4880]},{"content":"App manifest compliance test","pos":[4885,4913]},{"content":"Test the contents of app manifest to make sure its contents are correct.","pos":[4915,4987]},{"content":"Background","pos":[4993,5003]},{"content":"Apps must have a correctly formatted app manifest.","pos":[5005,5055]},{"content":"Test details","pos":[5061,5073]},{"pos":[5075,5241],"content":"Examines the app manifest to verify the contents are correct as described in the <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>App package requirements<ept id=\"p1\">](https://msdn.microsoft.com/library/windows/apps/Mt148525)</ept>.","source":"Examines the app manifest to verify the contents are correct as described in the [App package requirements](https://msdn.microsoft.com/library/windows/apps/Mt148525)."},{"content":"File extensions and protocols","pos":[5249,5278]},{"content":"Your app can declare the file extensions that it wants to associate with.","pos":[5286,5359]},{"content":"Used improperly, an app can declare a large number of file extensions, most of which it may not even use, resulting in a bad user experience.","pos":[5360,5501]},{"content":"This test will add a check to limit the number of file extensions that an app can associate with.","pos":[5502,5599]},{"content":"Framework Dependency rule","pos":[5607,5632]},{"content":"This test enforces the requirement that apps take appropriate dependencies on the UWP.","pos":[5640,5726]},{"content":"If there is an inappropriate dependency, this test will fail.","pos":[5727,5788]},{"content":"If there is a mismatch between the OS version the app applies to and the framework dependencies made, the test will fail.","pos":[5794,5915]},{"content":"The test would also fail if the app refers to any preview versions of the framework dlls.","pos":[5916,6005]},{"content":"Inter-process Communication (IPC) verification","pos":[6013,6059]},{"content":"This test enforces the requirement that Windows Store apps do not communicate outside of the app container to Desktop components.","pos":[6067,6196]},{"content":"Inter-process communication is intended for side-loaded apps only.","pos":[6197,6263]},{"content":"Apps that specify the <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt><bpt id=\"p2\">**</bpt>ActivatableClassAttribute<ept id=\"p2\">**</ept><ept id=\"p1\">](https://msdn.microsoft.com/library/windows/apps/BR211414)</ept> with name equal to \"DesktopApplicationPath\" will fail this test.","pos":[6264,6440],"source":" Apps that specify the [**ActivatableClassAttribute**](https://msdn.microsoft.com/library/windows/apps/BR211414) with name equal to \"DesktopApplicationPath\" will fail this test."},{"content":"Corrective action","pos":[6446,6463]},{"pos":[6465,6618],"content":"Review the app's manifest against the requirements described in the <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>App package requirements<ept id=\"p1\">](https://msdn.microsoft.com/library/windows/apps/Mt148525)</ept>.","source":"Review the app's manifest against the requirements described in the [App package requirements](https://msdn.microsoft.com/library/windows/apps/Mt148525)."},{"content":"Windows Security features test","pos":[6623,6653]},{"content":"Background","pos":[6659,6669]},{"content":"Changing the default Windows security protections can put customers at increased risk.","pos":[6671,6757]},{"content":"Test details","pos":[6763,6775]},{"pos":[6777,6855],"content":"Tests the app's security by running the <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>BinScope Binary Analyzer<ept id=\"p1\">](#binscope)</ept>.","source":"Tests the app's security by running the [BinScope Binary Analyzer](#binscope)."},{"content":"The BinScope Binary Analyzer tests examine the app's binary files to check for coding and building practices that make the app less vulnerable to attack or to being used as an attack vector.","pos":[6857,7047]},{"content":"The BinScope Binary Analyzer tests check for the correct use of the following security-related features.","pos":[7049,7153]},{"content":"BinScope Binary Analyzer tests","pos":[7159,7189]},{"content":"Private Code Signing","pos":[7194,7214]},{"content":"BinScope Binary Analyzer tests","pos":[7220,7250]},{"pos":[7252,7493],"content":"The <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>BinScope Binary Analyzer<ept id=\"p1\">](http://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/p/?linkid=257276)</ept> tests examine the app's binary files to check for coding and building practices that make the app less vulnerable to attack or to being used as an attack vector.","source":"The [BinScope Binary Analyzer](http://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/p/?linkid=257276) tests examine the app's binary files to check for coding and building practices that make the app less vulnerable to attack or to being used as an attack vector."},{"content":"The BinScope Binary Analyzer tests check for the correct use of these security-related features:","pos":[7495,7591]},{"content":"AllowPartiallyTrustedCallersAttribute","pos":[7598,7635]},{"content":"/SafeSEH Exception Handling Protection","pos":[7655,7693]},{"content":"Data Execution Prevention","pos":[7713,7738]},{"content":"Address Space Layout Randomization","pos":[7758,7792]},{"content":"Read/Write Shared PE Section","pos":[7812,7840]},{"content":"AppContainerCheck","pos":[7860,7877]},{"content":"ExecutableImportsCheck","pos":[7904,7926]},{"content":"WXCheck","pos":[7946,7953]},{"pos":[8002,8039],"content":"AllowPartiallyTrustedCallersAttribute"},{"pos":[8041,8112],"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Windows App Certification Kit error message:<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> APTCACheck Test failed","source":"**Windows App Certification Kit error message:** APTCACheck Test failed"},{"content":"The AllowPartiallyTrustedCallersAttribute (APTCA) attribute enables access to fully trusted code from partially trusted code in signed assemblies.","pos":[8114,8260]},{"content":"When you apply the APTCA attribute to an assembly, partially trusted callers can access that assembly for the life of the assembly, which can compromise security.","pos":[8261,8423]},{"content":"What to do if your app fails this test","pos":[8427,8465]},{"content":"Don't use the APTCA attribute on strong named assemblies unless your project requires it and the risks are well understood.","pos":[8469,8592]},{"content":"In cases where it's required, make sure that all APIs are protected with appropriate code access security demands.","pos":[8593,8707]},{"content":"APTCA has no effect when the assembly is a part of a Universal Windows Platform (UWP) app.","pos":[8708,8798]},{"content":"Remarks","pos":[8802,8809]},{"content":"This test is performed only on managed code (C\\#, .NET, etc.).","pos":[8813,8875]},{"pos":[8910,8948],"content":"/SafeSEH Exception Handling Protection"},{"pos":[8950,9023],"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Windows App Certification Kit error message:<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> SafeSEHCheck Test failed","source":"**Windows App Certification Kit error message:** SafeSEHCheck Test failed"},{"content":"An exception handler runs when the app encounters an exceptional condition, such as a divide-by-zero error.","pos":[9025,9132]},{"content":"Because the address of the exception handler is stored on the stack when a function is called, it could be vulnerable to a buffer overflow attacker if some malicious software were to overwrite the stack.","pos":[9133,9336]},{"content":"What to do if your app fails this test","pos":[9340,9378]},{"content":"Enable the /SAFESEH option in the linker command when you build your app.","pos":[9382,9455]},{"content":"This option is on by default in the Release configurations of Visual Studio.","pos":[9456,9532]},{"content":"Verify this option is enabled in the build instructions for all executable modules in your app.","pos":[9533,9628]},{"content":"Remarks","pos":[9632,9639]},{"content":"The test is not performed on 64-bit binaries or ARM chipset binaries because they don't store exception handler addresses on the stack.","pos":[9643,9778]},{"pos":[9813,9838],"content":"Data Execution Prevention"},{"pos":[9840,9908],"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Windows App Certification Kit error message:<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> NXCheck Test failed","source":"**Windows App Certification Kit error message:** NXCheck Test failed"},{"content":"This test verifies that an app doesn't run code that is stored in a data segment.","pos":[9910,9991]},{"content":"What to do if your app fails this test","pos":[9995,10033]},{"content":"Enable the /NXCOMPAT option in the linker command when you build your app.","pos":[10037,10111]},{"content":"This option is on by default in linker versions that support Data Execution Prevention (DEP).","pos":[10112,10205]},{"content":"Remarks","pos":[10209,10216]},{"content":"We recommend that you test your apps on a DEP-capable CPU and fix any failures you find that result from DEP.","pos":[10220,10329]},{"pos":[10364,10398],"content":"Address Space Layout Randomization"},{"pos":[10400,10468],"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Windows App Certification Kit error message:<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> DBCheck Test failed","source":"**Windows App Certification Kit error message:** DBCheck Test failed"},{"content":"Address Space Layout Randomization (ASLR) loads executable images into unpredictable locations in memory, which makes it harder for malicious software that expects a program to be loaded at a certain virtual address to operate predictably.","pos":[10470,10709]},{"content":"Your app and all components that your app uses must support ASLR.","pos":[10710,10775]},{"content":"What to do if your app fails this test","pos":[10779,10817]},{"content":"Enable the /DYNAMICBASE option in the linker command when you build your app.","pos":[10821,10898]},{"content":"Verify that all modules that your app uses also use this linker option.","pos":[10899,10970]},{"content":"Remarks","pos":[10974,10981]},{"content":"Normally, ASLR doesn't affect performance.","pos":[10985,11027]},{"content":"But in some scenarios there is a slight performance improvement on 32-bit systems.","pos":[11028,11110]},{"content":"It is possible that performance could degrade in a highly congested system that have many images loaded in many different memory locations.","pos":[11111,11250]},{"content":"This test is performed on only apps written in managed code, such as by using C\\# or .NET Framework.","pos":[11252,11352]},{"pos":[11387,11415],"content":"Read/Write Shared PE Section"},{"pos":[11417,11498],"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Windows App Certification Kit error message:<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> SharedSectionsCheck Test failed.","source":"**Windows App Certification Kit error message:** SharedSectionsCheck Test failed."},{"content":"Binary files with writable sections that are marked as shared are a security threat.","pos":[11500,11584]},{"content":"Don't build apps with shared writable sections unless necessary.","pos":[11585,11649]},{"content":"Use <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt><bpt id=\"p2\">**</bpt>CreateFileMapping<ept id=\"p2\">**</ept><ept id=\"p1\">](https://msdn.microsoft.com/library/windows/desktop/Aa366537)</ept> or <bpt id=\"p3\">[</bpt><bpt id=\"p4\">**</bpt>MapViewOfFile<ept id=\"p4\">**</ept><ept id=\"p3\">](https://msdn.microsoft.com/library/windows/desktop/Aa366761)</ept> to create a properly secured shared memory object.","pos":[11650,11873],"source":" Use [**CreateFileMapping**](https://msdn.microsoft.com/library/windows/desktop/Aa366537) or [**MapViewOfFile**](https://msdn.microsoft.com/library/windows/desktop/Aa366761) to create a properly secured shared memory object."},{"content":"What to do if your app fails this test","pos":[11877,11915]},{"pos":[11919,12234],"content":"Remove any shared sections from the app and create shared memory objects by calling <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt><bpt id=\"p2\">**</bpt>CreateFileMapping<ept id=\"p2\">**</ept><ept id=\"p1\">](https://msdn.microsoft.com/library/windows/desktop/Aa366537)</ept> or <bpt id=\"p3\">[</bpt><bpt id=\"p4\">**</bpt>MapViewOfFile<ept id=\"p4\">**</ept><ept id=\"p3\">](https://msdn.microsoft.com/library/windows/desktop/Aa366761)</ept> with the proper security attributes and then rebuild your app.","source":"Remove any shared sections from the app and create shared memory objects by calling [**CreateFileMapping**](https://msdn.microsoft.com/library/windows/desktop/Aa366537) or [**MapViewOfFile**](https://msdn.microsoft.com/library/windows/desktop/Aa366761) with the proper security attributes and then rebuild your app."},{"content":"Remarks","pos":[12238,12245]},{"content":"This test is performed only on apps written in unmanaged languages, such as by using C or C++.","pos":[12249,12343]},{"content":"AppContainerCheck","pos":[12349,12366]},{"pos":[12368,12447],"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Windows App Certification Kit error message:<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> AppContainerCheck Test failed.","source":"**Windows App Certification Kit error message:** AppContainerCheck Test failed."},{"content":"The AppContainerCheck verifies that the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>appcontainer<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> bit in the portable executable (PE) header of an executable binary is set.","pos":[12449,12580],"source":"The AppContainerCheck verifies that the **appcontainer** bit in the portable executable (PE) header of an executable binary is set."},{"content":"Apps must have the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>appcontainer<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> bit set on all .exe files and all unmanaged DLLs to execute properly.","pos":[12581,12686],"source":" Apps must have the **appcontainer** bit set on all .exe files and all unmanaged DLLs to execute properly."},{"content":"What to do if your app fails this test","pos":[12690,12728]},{"pos":[12732,12905],"content":"If a native executable file fails the test, make sure that you used the latest compiler and linker to build the file and that you use the <bpt id=\"p1\">*</bpt>/appcontainer<ept id=\"p1\">*</ept> flag on the linker.","source":"If a native executable file fails the test, make sure that you used the latest compiler and linker to build the file and that you use the */appcontainer* flag on the linker."},{"content":"If a managed executable fails the test, make sure that you used the latest compiler and linker, such as Microsoft Visual Studio, to build the Windows Store app.","pos":[12907,13067]},{"content":"Remarks","pos":[13071,13078]},{"content":"This test is performed on all .exe files and on unmanaged DLLs.","pos":[13082,13145]},{"pos":[13180,13202],"content":"ExecutableImportsCheck"},{"pos":[13204,13288],"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Windows App Certification Kit error message:<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> ExecutableImportsCheck Test failed.","source":"**Windows App Certification Kit error message:** ExecutableImportsCheck Test failed."},{"content":"A portable executable (PE) image fails this test if its import table has been placed in an executable code section.","pos":[13290,13405]},{"content":"This can occur if you enabled .rdata merging for the PE image by setting the <bpt id=\"p1\">*</bpt>/merge<ept id=\"p1\">*</ept> flag of the Visual C++ linker as <bpt id=\"p2\">*</bpt>/merge:.rdata=.text<ept id=\"p2\">*</ept>.","pos":[13406,13547],"source":" This can occur if you enabled .rdata merging for the PE image by setting the */merge* flag of the Visual C++ linker as */merge:.rdata=.text*."},{"content":"What to do if your app fails this test","pos":[13551,13589]},{"content":"Don't merge the import table into an executable code section.","pos":[13593,13654]},{"content":"Make sure that the <bpt id=\"p1\">*</bpt>/merge<ept id=\"p1\">*</ept> flag of the Visual C++ linker is not set to merge the “.rdata” section into a code section.","pos":[13655,13774],"source":" Make sure that the */merge* flag of the Visual C++ linker is not set to merge the “.rdata” section into a code section."},{"content":"Remarks","pos":[13778,13785]},{"content":"This test is performed on all binary code except purely managed assemblies.","pos":[13789,13864]},{"pos":[13899,13906],"content":"WXCheck"},{"pos":[13908,13977],"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Windows App Certification Kit error message:<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> WXCheck Test failed.","source":"**Windows App Certification Kit error message:** WXCheck Test failed."},{"content":"The check helps to ensure that a binary does not have any pages that are mapped as writable and executable.","pos":[13979,14086]},{"content":"This can occur if the binary has a writable and executable section or if the binary’s <bpt id=\"p1\">*</bpt>SectionAlignment<ept id=\"p1\">*</ept> is less than <bpt id=\"p2\">*</bpt>PAGE\\-SIZE<ept id=\"p2\">*</ept>.","pos":[14087,14218],"source":" This can occur if the binary has a writable and executable section or if the binary’s *SectionAlignment* is less than *PAGE\\-SIZE*."},{"content":"What to do if your app fails this test","pos":[14222,14260]},{"pos":[14264,14423],"content":"Make sure that the binary does not have a writeable or executable section and that the binary's <bpt id=\"p1\">*</bpt>SectionAlignment<ept id=\"p1\">*</ept> value is at least equal to its <bpt id=\"p2\">*</bpt>PAGE\\-SIZE<ept id=\"p2\">*</ept>.","source":"Make sure that the binary does not have a writeable or executable section and that the binary's *SectionAlignment* value is at least equal to its *PAGE\\-SIZE*."},{"content":"Remarks","pos":[14427,14434]},{"content":"This test is performed on all .exe files and on native, unmanaged DLLs.","pos":[14438,14509]},{"content":"An executable may have a writable and executable section if it has been built with Edit and Continue enabled (/ZI).","pos":[14511,14626]},{"content":"Disabling Edit and Continue will cause the invalid section to not be present.","pos":[14627,14704]},{"pos":[14706,14769],"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">*</bpt>PAGE\\-SIZE<ept id=\"p1\">*</ept> is the default <bpt id=\"p2\">*</bpt>SectionAlignment<ept id=\"p2\">*</ept> for executables.","source":"*PAGE\\-SIZE* is the default *SectionAlignment* for executables."},{"content":"Private Code Signing","pos":[14775,14795]},{"content":"Tests for the existence of private code signing binaries within the app package.","pos":[14797,14877]},{"content":"Background","pos":[14883,14893]},{"content":"Private code signing files should be kept private as they may be used for malicious purposes in the event they are compromised.","pos":[14895,15022]},{"content":"Test details","pos":[15028,15040]},{"content":"Tests for files within the app package that have an extension of .pfx or.snk that would indicate that private signing keys were included.","pos":[15042,15179]},{"content":"Corrective actions","pos":[15185,15203]},{"content":"Remove any private code signing keys (e.g. .pfx and .snk files) from the package.","pos":[15205,15286]},{"content":"Supported API test","pos":[15291,15309]},{"content":"Test the app for the use of any non-compliant APIs.","pos":[15311,15362]},{"content":"Background","pos":[15368,15378]},{"content":"Apps must use the APIs for Windows Store apps (Windows Runtime or supported Win32 APIs) to be certified for the Windows Store.","pos":[15380,15506]},{"content":"This test also identifies situations where a managed binary takes a dependency on a function outside of the approved profile.","pos":[15507,15632]},{"content":"Test details","pos":[15638,15650]},{"content":"Verifies that each binary within the app package doesn't have a dependency on a Win32 API that is not supported for Windows Store app development by checking the import address table of the binary.","pos":[15656,15853]},{"content":"Verifies that each managed binary within the app package doesn't have a dependency on a function outside of the approved profile.","pos":[15858,15987]},{"content